decision_conditions:
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;
mso-fareast-font-family:Calibri">3.&nbsp;&nbsp; <u>Construction
Environmental Management Plan (CEMP) and Site Waste Management Plan (SWMP)<o:p></o:p></u></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;
mso-fareast-font-family:Calibri"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;
mso-fareast-font-family:Calibri">No development shall commence until an updated
Construction Environmental Management Plan (CEMP) and a Site Waste Management
Plan (SWMP) based on the Construction Management Plan, Version 1 dated 17 March
2019, prepared by Weller Designs Ltd has been submitted to and approved in
writing by the Local Planning Authority.&nbsp;
These Plans shall incorporate details of:<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;
mso-fareast-font-family:Calibri"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left:14.2pt;text-indent:-14.2pt;tab-stops:
21.3pt"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;
mso-fareast-font-family:Calibri">a)&nbsp;
construction traffic management;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left:14.2pt;text-indent:-14.2pt"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:
Calibri">b)&nbsp; the parking of vehicles of
site operatives and visitors;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left:14.2pt;text-indent:-14.2pt"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:
Calibri">c)&nbsp; loading and unloading of
plant and materials;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left:14.2pt;text-indent:-14.2pt"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:
Calibri">d)&nbsp; storage of plant and
materials used in constructing the development;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left:14.2pt;text-indent:-14.2pt"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:
Calibri">e)&nbsp; the erection and maintenance
of security hoarding(s) including decorative displays and facilities for public
viewing, where appropriate;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left:14.2pt;text-indent:-14.2pt"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:
Calibri">f)&nbsp;&nbsp; wheel washing facilities;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left:14.2pt;text-indent:-14.2pt"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:
Calibri">g)&nbsp; measures to control the
emission of dust, dirt and emissions to air during construction; such measures
to accord with the guidance provided in the document “The Control of Dust and
Emissions during Construction and Demolition”, Mayor of London, July 2014;
including but not confined to non-road mobile machinery (NRMM) requirements;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left:14.2pt;text-indent:-14.2pt"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:
Calibri">(h) </span><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;
mso-fareast-language:EN-GB">a construction phase air quality monitoring plan
which accords with the advice provided in document “</span><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif">Guidance on Monitoring
in the Vicinity of Demolition and Construction Sites Institute of Air Quality
Management” October 2018 (version 1.1).&nbsp;
The plan shall include, but not be confined to, site action levels to be
used to ensure that dust mitigation measures are both adequate and are being
applied correctly;</span><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;
mso-fareast-font-family:Calibri"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left:14.2pt;text-indent:-14.2pt"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:
Calibri">i)&nbsp;&nbsp; noise and vibration
control;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left:14.2pt;text-indent:-14.2pt"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:
Calibri">j)&nbsp;&nbsp; a scheme for
recycling/disposing of waste resulting from demolition and construction works;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left:14.2pt;text-indent:-14.2pt"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:
Calibri">k)&nbsp; the use of efficient
construction materials;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left:14.2pt;text-indent:-14.2pt"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:
Calibri">l)&nbsp;&nbsp; methods to minimise waste,
to encourage re-use, recovery and recycling, and sourcing of materials; and<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left:14.2pt;text-indent:-14.2pt"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:
Calibri">m)&nbsp; a nominated
Developer/Resident Liaison Representative with an address and contact telephone
number to be circulated to those residents consulted on the application by the
developer’s representatives.&nbsp; This person
will act as first point of contact for residents who have any problems or
questions related to the ongoing development.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left:14.2pt;text-indent:-14.2pt"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:
Calibri"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;
mso-fareast-font-family:Calibri">Construction work and associated activities
are only to be carried out between the hours of 08:00 and 18:00 Monday to
Friday and 08:00 and 13:00 Saturday, with no work on Sundays or public holidays
without the prior written permission of the Local Planning Authority.&nbsp; Any works which are associated with the
generation of ground borne vibration are only to be carried out between the
hours of 08:00 and 18:00 Monday to Friday. <o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;
mso-fareast-font-family:Calibri"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;
mso-fareast-language:EN-GB">Construction work and associated activities are to
be carried out in accordance with the recommendations contained within British
Standard 5228:2014, “Code of practice for noise and vibration control on
construction and open sites”, Parts 1 and 2.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;
mso-fareast-language:EN-GB"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;
mso-fareast-language:EN-GB">If ground improvement work is undertaken pursuant
to this permission then the 5% level of vibration attributable these activities
shall not exceed a peak particle velocity of 1.5mm/sec when measured at the
point of entry to any adjoining sensitive development.&nbsp; In the event of reasonable complaint of
vibration nuisance and at the request of the Local Planning Authority,
monitoring to evaluate compliance with this condition is to be carried out and
the results submitted to the Local Planning Authority.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;
mso-fareast-font-family:Calibri"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p>















































</p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;
mso-fareast-font-family:Calibri">Once approved the Plans shall be adhered to
throughout the construction period for the development.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;
mso-fareast-language:EN-GB">6.&nbsp; <u>Contaminated
Land and Remediation<o:p></o:p></u></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;
mso-fareast-language:EN-GB">No development shall commence until:<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;
mso-fareast-language:EN-GB"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;
mso-fareast-language:EN-GB">(a) a</span><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size:11.0pt;
font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:
EN-GB">n investigation and risk assessment, in addition to any assessment
provided with the planning application, has been completed in accordance with a
scheme to assess the nature and extent of any contamination on the site,
whether or not it originates on the site.&nbsp; The contents of the scheme are
subject to the approval in writing of the Local Planning Authority.&nbsp; The
investigation and risk assessment must be undertaken by competent persons and a
written report of the findings must be produced.&nbsp; The written report is
subject to the approval in writing of the Local Planning Authority.&nbsp; The
report of the findings must include:<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;
mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left:35.45pt;text-indent:-14.15pt;text-autospace:
none"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:
EN-GB">(i)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; a survey of the extent, scale and nature of
contamination;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left:42.55pt;text-indent:-21.25pt;text-autospace:
none"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:
EN-GB">(ii)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; an assessment of the potential risks to human
health; property (existing or proposed) including buildings, crops, livestock,
pets, woodland and service lines and pipes; adjoining land; groundwaters and
surface waters; ecological systems; archaeological sites and ancient monuments;
and<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left:35.45pt;text-indent:-14.15pt;text-autospace:
none"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:
EN-GB">(iii)&nbsp;&nbsp; an appraisal of remedial options, and proposal of the
preferred option(s). <o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left:35.45pt;text-indent:-14.15pt;text-autospace:
none"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:
EN-GB"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;
font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB">This must be
conducted in accordance with DEFRA and the Environment Agency’s ‘Model
Procedures for the Management of Land Contamination, CLR 11’; and<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;
font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;
font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB">(b)&nbsp;&nbsp; a
detailed remediation scheme, to bring the site to a condition suitable for the
intended use by removing unacceptable risks to human health, buildings and
other property and the natural and historical environment, has been prepared
and submitted to the Local Planning Authority for approval in writing.&nbsp;
The scheme must include all works to be undertaken, proposed remediation
objectives and remediation criteria, timetable of works and site management
procedures.&nbsp; The scheme must ensure that the site will not qualify as contaminated
land under Part 2A of the Environmental Protection Act 1990 in relation to the
intended use of the land after remediation. <o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;
font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;
font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB">(c)&nbsp; The
approved remediation scheme must be carried out in accordance with its terms
prior to commencement of the development, other than that required to carry out
remediation, unless otherwise agreed in writing by the Local Planning
Authority.&nbsp; The Local Planning Authority must be given two weeks written
notification of commencement of the remediation scheme works.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;
font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;
font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB">Following completion
of measures identified in the approved remediation scheme, a verification
report that demonstrates the effectiveness of the remediation carried out must
be produced and is subject to the approval in writing of the Local Planning
Authority.&nbsp; The report shall include results of sampling and monitoring
carried out to demonstrate that the site remediation criteria have been met.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;
font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p>



































</p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-right:19.3pt;text-autospace:none"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:
EN-GB">(d)&nbsp;&nbsp; In the event that contamination is found at any time
when carrying out the approved development that was not previously identified
it must be reported in writing immediately to the Local Planning
Authority.&nbsp; An investigation and risk assessment must be undertaken in
accordance with the requirements of (a), and where remediation is necessary a
remediation scheme must be prepared in accordance with the requirements of (b),
which is subject to the approval in writing of the Local Planning
Authority.&nbsp; Following completion of measures identified in the approved
remediation scheme a verification report must be prepared, which is subject to
the approval in writing of the Local Planning Authority.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">11.&nbsp; <u>Crime
Prevention Scheme</u><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p>



</p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">The development hereby permitted shall achieve a
Certificate of Compliance in respect of the Secured by Design scheme (silver),
or alternatively achieve security standards (based on Secured by Design
principles) to the satisfaction of the Metropolitan Police, details of which
shall be provided to the Local Planning Authority for its written approval
prior to the first use of the approved development.&nbsp; All security measures applied to the approved
development shall be permanently retained thereafter.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:
Calibri">12.&nbsp; <u>Travel Plan</u><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:
Calibri"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:
Calibri">Prior to the first use of the development hereby permitted, a Travel
Plan for the site which shall include proposals for minimising car-borne travel
and encouraging walking, cycling and the use of public transport shall be
submitted to the Local Planning Authority for approval in writing.&nbsp; The Travel Plan shall include details of
funding, implementation, monitoring and review.&nbsp;
The approved Travel Plan shall be implemented and monitored in
accordance with the approved scheme.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p>





</p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:
Calibri"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>
description: Upgrade of park landscape and provision of new park facilities comprising a new toddler playground, a new adventure playground zone, an interactive maze and associated grass amphitheatre/picnic zone, new nature zones incorporating wetlands, wildflower meadow and native planting, areas designated for public art and new network of paths.
